item.title: $48m boost to virus mental health services
item.description: More Australians will be able to access mental health services with the federal government boosting funding by $48.1 million.

item.title: Boral says earnings down 3-5pct in 2020
item.description: Boral says its earnings for January to April have been down three to five per cent compared to the first half as it weathers the coronavirus crisis.

item.title: Millions of Wuhan residents tested: China
item.description: Wuhan, the original epicentre of the new coronavirus outbreak in China, has tested over three million residents for the pathogen since April, and will now focus its testing efforts on the rest of its 11 million population, according to state media.

item.title: Vic treasurer eyes off post-war approach
item.description: Victoria's treasurer plans to take a post-wartime approach to getting the state economy moving again in the aftermath of the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Global coronavirus toll ‘passes 300,000’
item.description: Global coronavirus deaths have passed 300,000 as infections approached 4.5 million, according to a Reuters tally, with the United States responsible for more than a quarter of all fatalities.

item.title: Virus case numbers will grow: NSW Premier
item.description: NSW Premier Gladys Berejiklian has warned case numbers of COVID-19 in the state will inevitably rise in the coming weeks as restrictions on gatherings and pubs, clubs, cafes, restaurants and places of worship are eased.

item.title: NSW woman trading Bitcoin for cash charged
item.description: A woman who allegedly exchanged cash for cryptocurrency and transacted more than $5 million worth of Bitcoin has been charged.

item.title: Delay to NSW HSC after ‘challenging’ year
item.description: Year 12 students across NSW will start their HSC exams five days later than planned after a "challenging year" amid the COVID-19 pandemic.

item.title: Project to bring bushfire images together
item.description: Photos and videos that capture the harrowing experiences of Australia's bushfires crisis and the recovery efforts will be brought together so future generations understand what happened.
